        Converts an IMarketDataValue to a StandardValue.

        Eventually we should convert the market data code over to use IValue's.

        Parameters:
        v - StandardValue to be copied into.
        mdValue - Value being copied from.
        impliedDecimals - Number of implied decimal places to use in converting market data long values into StandardValue's.

      • isNone

        public boolean isNone()
        Description copied from interface: IMarketDataValue
        Returns true if the value is the special value representing "none". The special values representing "none" are as follows:
        • long - IInstrument.VALUE_NONE
        • BytesSegment - length == 0
        • String - length == 0
        Specified by:
        isNone in interface IMarketDataValue
        Returns:
        True if no value.

      • isUndefined

        public boolean isUndefined()
        Description copied from interface: IMarketDataValue
        Returns true if the value is the special value representing "undefined". The special values representing "undefined" are as follows:
        • long - IInstrument.VALUE_UNKNOWN
        • BytesSegment - null || length < 0
        • String - null

        Note that the type can be defined (eg long) but the value is undefined (eg long value == IInstrument.VALUE_UNKNOWN).

        Specified by:
        isUndefined in interface IMarketDataValue
        Returns:
        True if value is undefined.
